==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Runic
<hw>Ru"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to a
rune, to runes, or to the Norsemen; <as>as, <ex>runic</ex> verses;
<ex>runic</ex> letters; <ex>runic</ex> names; <ex>runic</ex>
rhyme</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Runic staff</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Clog almanac</cref>,
under <er>Clog</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Runic wand</b></col>, <cd>a willow
wand bearing runes, formerly thought to have been used by the heathen
tribes of Northern Europe in magical ceremonies.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Run-in</ent>⟦br⟧
